enums.name: ClientEventType
enums.doc: Client event types used in VoiceLive protocol.

enums.name: AnimationOutputType
enums.doc: Specifies the types of animation data to output.

enums.name: AudioTimestampType

values.name: word
values.doc: Timestamps per word in the output audio.

enums.doc: Output timestamp types supported in audio response content.

enums.name: ToolType
enums.doc:
The supported tool type discriminators for voicelive tools.
Currently, only 'function' tools are supported.

enums.name: ToolChoiceLiteral

values.name: auto
values.doc: Specifies that the model should freely determine which tool or tools, if any, to call.

values.name: none
values.doc: Specifies that the model should call no tools whatsoever.

values.name: required
values.doc: Specifies that the model should call at least one tool.

enums.doc: The available set of mode-level, string literal tool_choice options for the voicelive endpoint.

enums.name: ServerEventType
enums.doc: Server event types used in VoiceLive protocol.

models.name: ClientEventSessionUpdate
models.doc:
Send this event to update the sessions default configuration.
The client may send this event at any time to update any field,
except for `voice`. However, note that once a session has been
initialized with a particular `model`, it cant be changed to
another model using `session.update`.

When the server receives a `session.update`, it will respond
with a `session.updated` event showing the full, effective configuration.
Only the fields that are present are updated. To clear a field like
`instructions`, pass an empty string.

input_audio_buffer.append.name: ClientEventInputAudioBufferAppend
input_audio_buffer.append.doc:
Send this event to append audio bytes to the input audio buffer. The audio
buffer is temporary storage you can write to and later commit. In Server VAD
mode, the audio buffer is used to detect speech and the server will decide
when to commit. When Server VAD is disabled, you must commit the audio buffer
manually.

The client may choose how much audio to place in each event up to a maximum
of 15 MiB, for example streaming smaller chunks from the client may allow the
VAD to be more responsive. Unlike made other client events, the server will
not send a confirmation response to this event.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be `input_audio_buffer.append`.

properties.name: audio
properties.doc:
Base64-encoded audio. This must be in the format specified by the
`input_audio_format` field in the session configuration.

input_audio_buffer.commit.name: ClientEventInputAudioBufferCommit
input_audio_buffer.commit.doc:
Send this event to commit the user input audio buffer, which will create a
new user message item in the conversation. This event will produce an error
if the input audio buffer is empty. When in Server VAD mode, the client does
not need to send this event, the server will commit the audio buffer
automatically.

Committing the input audio buffer will trigger input audio transcription
(if enabled in session configuration), but it will not create a response
from the model. The server will respond with an `input_audio_buffer.committed`
event.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be `input_audio_buffer.commit`.

input_audio_buffer.clear.name: ClientEventInputAudioBufferClear
input_audio_buffer.clear.doc:
Send this event to clear the audio bytes in the buffer. The server will
respond with an `input_audio_buffer.cleared` event.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be `input_audio_buffer.clear`.

input_audio.turn.start.name: ClientEventInputAudioTurnStart
input_audio.turn.start.doc: Indicates the start of a new audio input turn.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be 'input_audio.turn.start'.

properties.name: turn_id
properties.doc: Unique identifier for the input audio turn.

input_audio.turn.append.name: ClientEventInputAudioTurnAppend
input_audio.turn.append.doc: Appends audio data to an ongoing input turn.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be 'input_audio.turn.append'.

properties.name: turn_id
properties.doc: The ID of the turn this audio is part of.

properties.name: audio
properties.doc: Base64-encoded audio chunk.

input_audio.turn.end.name: ClientEventInputAudioTurnEnd
input_audio.turn.end.doc: Marks the end of an audio input turn.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be 'input_audio.turn.end'.

properties.name: turn_id
properties.doc: The ID of the audio turn being ended.

input_audio.turn.cancel.name: ClientEventInputAudioTurnCancel
input_audio.turn.cancel.doc: Cancels an in-progress input audio turn.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be 'input_audio.turn.cancel'.

properties.name: turn_id
properties.doc: The ID of the turn to cancel.

input_audio.clear.name: ClientEventInputAudioClear
input_audio.clear.doc: Clears all input audio currently being streamed.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be 'input_audio.clear'.

conversation.item.create.name: ClientEventConversationItemCreate
conversation.item.create.doc:
Add a new Item to the Conversation's context, including messages, function
calls, and function call responses. This event can be used both to populate a
"history" of the conversation and to add new items mid-stream, but has the
current limitation that it cannot populate assistant audio messages.

If successful, the server will respond with a `conversation.item.created`
event, otherwise an `error` event will be sent.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be `conversation.item.create`.

properties.name: event_id
properties.doc: Optional client-generated ID used to identify this event.

properties.name: previous_item_id
properties.doc:
The ID of the preceding item after which the new item will be inserted.
If not set, the new item will be appended to the end of the conversation.
If set to `root`, the new item will be added to the beginning of the conversation.
If set to an existing ID, it allows an item to be inserted mid-conversation. If the
ID cannot be found, an error will be returned and the item will not be added.

type.name: ConversationRequestItem
type.doc: Base for any response item; discriminated by `type`.

conversation.item.retrieve.name: ClientEventConversationItemRetrieve
conversation.item.retrieve.doc:
Send this event when you want to retrieve the server's representation of a specific item in the conversation history. This is useful, for example, to inspect user audio after noise cancellation and VAD.
The server will respond with a `conversation.item.retrieved` event,
unless the item does not exist in the conversation history, in which case the
server will respond with an error.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be `conversation.item.retrieve`.

properties.name: item_id
properties.doc: The ID of the item to retrieve.

conversation.item.truncate.name: ClientEventConversationItemTruncate
conversation.item.truncate.doc:
Send this event to truncate a previous assistant messages audio. The server
will produce audio faster than voicelive, so this event is useful when the user
interrupts to truncate audio that has already been sent to the client but not
yet played. This will synchronize the server's understanding of the audio with
the client's playback.

Truncating audio will delete the server-side text transcript to ensure there
is not text in the context that hasn't been heard by the user.

If successful, the server will respond with a `conversation.item.truncated`
event.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be `conversation.item.truncate`.

properties.name: item_id
properties.doc:
The ID of the assistant message item to truncate. Only assistant message
items can be truncated.

properties.name: content_index
properties.doc: The index of the content part to truncate. Set this to 0.

properties.name: audio_end_ms
properties.doc:
Inclusive duration up to which audio is truncated, in milliseconds. If
the audio_end_ms is greater than the actual audio duration, the server
will respond with an error.

conversation.item.delete.name: ClientEventConversationItemDelete
conversation.item.delete.doc:
Send this event when you want to remove any item from the conversation
history. The server will respond with a `conversation.item.deleted` event,
unless the item does not exist in the conversation history, in which case the
server will respond with an error.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be `conversation.item.delete`.

properties.name: item_id
properties.doc: The ID of the item to delete.

response.create.name: ClientEventResponseCreate
response.create.doc:
This event instructs the server to create a Response, which means triggering
model inference. When in Server VAD mode, the server will create Responses
automatically.

A Response will include at least one Item, and may have two, in which case
the second will be a function call. These Items will be appended to the
conversation history.

The server will respond with a `response.created` event, events for Items
and content created, and finally a `response.done` event to indicate the
Response is complete.

The `response.create` event includes inference configuration like
`instructions`, and `temperature`. These fields will override the Session's
configuration for this Response only.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be `response.create`.

type.name: ResponseCreateParams
type.doc: Create a new VoiceLive response with these parameters

properties.name: commit
properties.doc: Whether to commit the response to the conversation. Defaults to true.

properties.name: cancel_previous
properties.doc: Whether to cancel any ongoing generation before starting this one. Defaults to true.

properties.name: append_input_items
properties.doc: Input items to append to the conversation context before generating a response.

properties.name: input_items
properties.doc:
Input items to be used as the context for this response.
An empty array clears previous context.

properties.name: modalities
properties.doc:
The set of modalities the model can respond with. To disable audio,
set this to ["text"].

properties.name: instructions
properties.doc:
The default system instructions (i.e. system message) prepended to model
calls. This field allows the client to guide the model on desired
responses. The model can be instructed on response content and format,
(e.g. "be extremely succinct", "act friendly", "here are examples of good
responses") and on audio behavior (e.g. "talk quickly", "inject emotion
into your voice", "laugh frequently"). The instructions are not guaranteed
to be followed by the model, but they provide guidance to the model on the
desired behavior.

Note that the server sets default instructions which will be used if this
field is not set and are visible in the `session.created` event at the
start of the session.

properties.name: voice
properties.doc: supported voice identifiers and configurations.

variantTypes.name: OpenAIVoice
variantTypes.doc:
OpenAI voice configuration with explicit type field.

This provides a unified interface for OpenAI voices, complementing the
existing string-based OAIVoice for backward compatibility.

properties.name: name
properties.doc: Voice name cannot be empty.

properties.name: endpoint_id
properties.doc: Endpoint ID cannot be empty.

properties.name: temperature
properties.doc: Temperature must be between 0.0 and 1.0.

properties.name: name
properties.doc: Voice name cannot be empty.

properties.name: temperature
properties.doc: Temperature must be between 0.0 and 1.0.

azure-platform.name: AzurePlatformVoice
azure-platform.doc: Azure platform voice configuration (variant of standard).

properties.name: name
properties.doc: Voice name cannot be empty.

properties.name: temperature
properties.doc: Temperature must be between 0.0 and 1.0.

properties.name: name
properties.doc: Voice name cannot be empty.

properties.name: temperature
properties.doc: Temperature must be between 0.0 and 1.0.

properties.name: model
properties.doc: Underlying neural model to use for personal voice.

variantTypes.name: LlmVoice
variantTypes.doc: Voice configuration for LLM (Large Language Model) voices.

properties.name: output_audio_format
properties.doc: The format of output audio. Options are `pcm16`, `g711_ulaw`, or `g711_alaw`.

properties.name: tools
properties.doc: Tools (functions) available to the model.

valueType.name: VoiceLiveToolDefinition
valueType.doc: The base representation of a voicelive tool definition.

function.name: VoiceLiveFunctionDefinition
function.doc: The definition of a function tool as used by the voicelive endpoint.

properties.name: tool_choice
properties.doc:
How the model chooses tools. Options are `auto`, `none`, `required`, or
specify a function, like `{"type": "function", "function": {"name": "my_function"}}`.

properties.name: temperature
properties.doc: Sampling temperature for the model, limited to [0.6, 1.2]. Defaults to 0.8.

properties.name: max_output_tokens
properties.doc:
Maximum number of output tokens for a single assistant response,
inclusive of tool calls. Provide an integer between 1 and 4096 to
limit output tokens, or `inf` for the maximum available tokens for a
given model. Defaults to `inf`.

properties.name: additional_instructions
properties.doc: additional instructions (system prompt) appended to the default instructions of the session. Only affects this response only.

response.cancel.name: ClientEventResponseCancel
response.cancel.doc:
Send this event to cancel an in-progress response. The server will respond
with a `response.cancelled` event or an error if there is no response to
cancel.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be `response.cancel`.

properties.name: response_id
properties.doc:
A specific response ID to cancel - if not provided, will cancel an
in-progress response in the default conversation.

session.avatar.connect.name: ClientEventSessionAvatarConnect
session.avatar.connect.doc:
Sent when the client connects and provides its SDP (Session Description Protocol)
  for avatar-related media negotiation.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be 'session.avatar.connect'.

properties.name: client_sdp
properties.doc: The client's SDP offer.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be `session.update`.

type.name: AnimationOptions
type.doc: Configuration for animation outputs including blendshapes, visemes, and emotion metadata.

properties.name: model_name
properties.doc: The name of the animation model to use.

properties.name: outputs
properties.doc: Set of output data types requested from the animation system.

properties.name: emotion_detection_interval_ms
properties.doc: Interval for emotion detection in milliseconds. If not set, emotion detection is disabled.

type.name: InputAudio
type.doc: Configuration for client audio input. Used to specify the audio model and optional phrase list.

properties.name: model
properties.doc: The name of the model to use for input audio (currently only 'azure-standard' is supported).

properties.name: phrase_list
properties.doc: Optional list of phrases to bias the speech recognition engine.

type.name: TurnDetection
type.doc: Top-level union for turn detection configuration.

server_vad.name: ServerVad
server_vad.doc: Base model for VAD-based turn detection.

type.name: EouDetection
type.doc: Top-level union for end-of-utterance (EOU) semantic detection configuration.

azure_semantic_vad.name: AzureSemanticVad
azure_semantic_vad.doc: Server Speech Detection (Azure semantic VAD, default variant).

azure_semantic_vad_en.name: AzureSemanticVadEn
azure_semantic_vad_en.doc: Server Speech Detection (Azure semantic VAD, English-only).

type.name: AudioNoiseReduction
type.doc: Configuration for input audio noise reduction.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The type of noise reduction model.

type.name: AudioEchoCancellation
type.doc: Echo cancellation configuration for server-side audio processing.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The type of echo cancellation model to use.

type.name: AvatarConfig
type.doc: Configuration for avatar streaming and behavior during the session.

properties.name: ice_servers
properties.doc: Optional list of ICE servers to use for WebRTC connection establishment.

valueType.name: IceServer
valueType.doc: ICE server configuration for WebRTC connection negotiation.

properties.name: Uris
properties.doc: List of ICE server URLs (e.g., TURN or STUN endpoints).

properties.name: username
properties.doc: Optional username used for authentication with the ICE server.

properties.name: credential
properties.doc: Optional credential (e.g., password or token) used for authentication.

properties.name: character
properties.doc: The character name or ID used for the avatar.

properties.name: style
properties.doc: Optional avatar style, such as emotional tone or speaking style.

properties.name: customized
properties.doc: Indicates whether the avatar is customized or not.

properties.name: video
properties.doc: Optional video configuration including resolution, bitrate, and codec.

properties.name: bitrate
properties.doc: Bitrate in bits per second (e.g., 2000000 for 2 Mbps).

properties.name: codec
properties.doc: Codec to use for encoding. Currently only 'h264' is supported.

properties.name: crop
properties.doc: Optional cropping settings for the video stream.

type.name: VideoCrop
type.doc: Defines a video crop rectangle using top-left and bottom-right coordinates.

properties.name: TopLeftInternal
properties.doc: Top-left corner of the crop region. Array of [x, y], must be non-negative integers.

properties.name: BottomRightInternal
properties.doc: Bottom-right corner of the crop region. Array of [x, y], must be non-negative integers.

properties.name: resolution
properties.doc: Optional resolution settings for the video stream.

type.name: VideoResolution
type.doc: Resolution of the video feed in pixels.

properties.name: width
properties.doc: Width of the video in pixels. Must be greater than 0.

properties.name: height
properties.doc: Height of the video in pixels. Must be greater than 0.

properties.name: model
properties.doc: The model used for transcription. E.g., 'whisper-1', 'azure-fast-transcription', 's2s-ingraph'.

properties.name: language
properties.doc: The language code to use for transcription, if specified.

properties.name: enabled
properties.doc: Whether transcription is enabled.

properties.name: custom_model
properties.doc: Whether a custom model is being used.

variantTypes.name: ToolChoiceObject
variantTypes.doc: A base representation for a voicelive tool_choice selecting a named tool.

function.name: ToolChoiceFunctionObject
function.doc: The representation of a voicelive tool_choice selecting a named function tool.

models.name: SessionUpdateSessionAvatarConnecting
models.doc: Sent when the server is in the process of establishing an avatar media connection and provides its SDP answer.

session.created.name: SessionUpdateSessionCreated
session.created.doc:
Returned when a Session is created. Emitted automatically when a new
connection is established as the first server event. This event will contain
the default Session configuration.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be `session.created`.

session.updated.name: SessionUpdateSessionUpdated
session.updated.doc:
Returned when a session is updated with a `session.update` event, unless
there is an error.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be `session.updated`.

error.name: SessionUpdateError
error.doc:
Returned when an error occurs, which could be a client problem or a server
problem. Most errors are recoverable and the session will stay open, we
recommend to implementors to monitor and log error messages by default.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be `error`.

properties.name: error
properties.doc: Details of the error.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The type of error (e.g., "invalid_request_error", "server_error").

properties.name: code
properties.doc: Error code, if any.

properties.name: message
properties.doc: A human-readable error message.

properties.name: param
properties.doc: Parameter related to the error, if any.

properties.name: event_id
properties.doc: The event_id of the client event that caused the error, if applicable.

response.text.delta.name: SessionUpdateResponseTextDelta
response.text.delta.doc: Returned when the text value of a "text" content part is updated.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be `response.text.delta`.

properties.name: response_id
properties.doc: The ID of the response.

properties.name: item_id
properties.doc: The ID of the item.

properties.name: output_index
properties.doc: The index of the output item in the response.

properties.name: content_index
properties.doc: The index of the content part in the item's content array.

properties.name: delta
properties.doc: The text delta.

response.audio.delta.name: SessionUpdateResponseAudioDelta
response.audio.delta.doc: Returned when the model-generated audio is updated.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be `response.audio.delta`.

properties.name: response_id
properties.doc: The ID of the response.

properties.name: item_id
properties.doc: The ID of the item.

properties.name: output_index
properties.doc: The index of the output item in the response.

properties.name: content_index
properties.doc: The index of the content part in the item's content array.

properties.name: delta
properties.doc: Base64-encoded audio data delta.

conversation.item.created.name: SessionUpdateConversationItemCreated
conversation.item.created.doc:
Returned when a conversation item is created. There are several scenarios that produce this event:
  - The server is generating a Response, which if successful will produce
    either one or two Items, which will be of type `message`
    (role `assistant`) or type `function_call`.
  - The input audio buffer has been committed, either by the client or the
    server (in `server_vad` mode). The server will take the content of the
    input audio buffer and add it to a new user message Item.
  - The client has sent a `conversation.item.create` event to add a new Item
    to the Conversation.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be `conversation.item.created`.

properties.name: previous_item_id
properties.doc:
The ID of the preceding item in the Conversation context, allows the
client to understand the order of the conversation.

conversation.item.deleted.name: SessionUpdateConversationItemDeleted
conversation.item.deleted.doc:
Returned when an item in the conversation is deleted by the client with a
`conversation.item.delete` event. This event is used to synchronize the
server's understanding of the conversation history with the client's view.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be `conversation.item.deleted`.

properties.name: item_id
properties.doc: The ID of the item that was deleted.

conversation.item.retrieved.name: SessionUpdateConversationItemRetrieved
conversation.item.retrieved.doc: Returned when a conversation item is retrieved with `conversation.item.retrieve`.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be `conversation.item.retrieved`.

conversation.item.truncated.name: SessionUpdateConversationItemTruncated
conversation.item.truncated.doc:
Returned when an earlier assistant audio message item is truncated by the
client with a `conversation.item.truncate` event. This event is used to
synchronize the server's understanding of the audio with the client's playback.

This action will truncate the audio and remove the server-side text transcript
to ensure there is no text in the context that hasn't been heard by the user.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be `conversation.item.truncated`.

properties.name: item_id
properties.doc: The ID of the assistant message item that was truncated.

properties.name: content_index
properties.doc: The index of the content part that was truncated.

properties.name: audio_end_ms
properties.doc: The duration up to which the audio was truncated, in milliseconds.

conversation.item.input_audio_transcript.name: SessionUpdateConversationItemInputAudioTranscriptionCompleted
conversation.item.input_audio_transcript.doc:
This event is the output of audio transcription for user audio written to the
user audio buffer. Transcription begins when the input audio buffer is
committed by the client or server (in `server_vad` mode). Transcription runs
asynchronously with Response creation, so this event may come before or after
the Response events.

VoiceLive API models accept audio natively, and thus input transcription is a
separate process run on a separate ASR (Automatic Speech Recognition) model.
The transcript may diverge somewhat from the model's interpretation, and
should be treated as a rough guide.

properties.name: type
properties.doc:
The event type, must be
`conversation.item.input_audio_transcription.completed`.

properties.name: item_id
properties.doc: The ID of the user message item containing the audio.

properties.name: content_index
properties.doc: The index of the content part containing the audio.

properties.name: transcript
properties.doc: The transcribed text.

conversation.item.input_audio_transcript.name: SessionUpdateConversationItemInputAudioTranscriptionDelta
conversation.item.input_audio_transcript.doc: Returned when the text value of an input audio transcription content part is updated.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be `conversation.item.input_audio_transcription.delta`.

properties.name: item_id
properties.doc: The ID of the item.

properties.name: content_index
properties.doc: The index of the content part in the item's content array.

properties.name: delta
properties.doc: The text delta.

properties.name: logprobs
properties.doc: The log probabilities of the transcription.

valueType.name: LogProbProperties
valueType.doc: A single log probability entry for a token.

properties.name: token
properties.doc: The token that was used to generate the log probability.

properties.name: logprob
properties.doc: The log probability of the token.

properties.name: bytes
properties.doc: The bytes that were used to generate the log probability.

conversation.item.input_audio_transcript.name: SessionUpdateConversationItemInputAudioTranscriptionFailed
conversation.item.input_audio_transcript.doc:
Returned when input audio transcription is configured, and a transcription
request for a user message failed. These events are separate from other
`error` events so that the client can identify the related Item.

properties.name: type
properties.doc:
The event type, must be
`conversation.item.input_audio_transcription.failed`.

properties.name: item_id
properties.doc: The ID of the user message item.

properties.name: content_index
properties.doc: The index of the content part containing the audio.

properties.name: error
properties.doc: Details of the transcription error.

type.name: VoiceLiveErrorDetails
type.doc: Error object returned in case of API failure.

properties.name: code
properties.doc: Error code, or null if unspecified.

properties.name: message
properties.doc: Human-readable error message.

properties.name: param
properties.doc: Parameter name related to the error, if applicable.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: Type or category of the error.

properties.name: event_id
properties.doc: Event id of the error.

input_audio_buffer.committed.name: SessionUpdateInputAudioBufferCommitted
input_audio_buffer.committed.doc:
Returned when an input audio buffer is committed, either by the client or
automatically in server VAD mode. The `item_id` property is the ID of the user
message item that will be created, thus a `conversation.item.created` event
will also be sent to the client.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be `input_audio_buffer.committed`.

properties.name: previous_item_id
properties.doc: The ID of the preceding item after which the new item will be inserted.

properties.name: item_id
properties.doc: The ID of the user message item that will be created.

input_audio_buffer.cleared.name: SessionUpdateInputAudioBufferCleared
input_audio_buffer.cleared.doc:
Returned when the input audio buffer is cleared by the client with a
`input_audio_buffer.clear` event.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be `input_audio_buffer.cleared`.

input_audio_buffer.speech_started.name: SessionUpdateInputAudioBufferSpeechStarted
input_audio_buffer.speech_started.doc:
Sent by the server when in `server_vad` mode to indicate that speech has been
detected in the audio buffer. This can happen any time audio is added to the
buffer (unless speech is already detected). The client may want to use this
event to interrupt audio playback or provide visual feedback to the user.

The client should expect to receive a `input_audio_buffer.speech_stopped` event
when speech stops. The `item_id` property is the ID of the user message item
that will be created when speech stops and will also be included in the
`input_audio_buffer.speech_stopped` event (unless the client manually commits
the audio buffer during VAD activation).

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be `input_audio_buffer.speech_started`.

properties.name: audio_start_ms
properties.doc:
Milliseconds from the start of all audio written to the buffer during the
session when speech was first detected. This will correspond to the
beginning of audio sent to the model, and thus includes the
`prefix_padding_ms` configured in the Session.

properties.name: item_id
properties.doc: The ID of the user message item that will be created when speech stops.

input_audio_buffer.speech_stopped.name: SessionUpdateInputAudioBufferSpeechStopped
input_audio_buffer.speech_stopped.doc:
Returned in `server_vad` mode when the server detects the end of speech in
the audio buffer. The server will also send an `conversation.item.created`
event with the user message item that is created from the audio buffer.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be `input_audio_buffer.speech_stopped`.

properties.name: audio_end_ms
properties.doc:
Milliseconds since the session started when speech stopped. This will
correspond to the end of audio sent to the model, and thus includes the
`min_silence_duration_ms` configured in the Session.

properties.name: item_id
properties.doc: The ID of the user message item that will be created.

response.created.name: SessionUpdateResponseCreated
response.created.doc:
Returned when a new Response is created. The first event of response creation,
where the response is in an initial state of `in_progress`.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be `response.created`.

properties.name: id
properties.doc: The unique ID of the response.

properties.name: object
properties.doc: The object type, must be `realtime.response`.

properties.name: status
properties.doc:
The final status of the response.
One of: `completed`, `cancelled`, `failed`, `incomplete`, or `in_progress`.

properties.name: status_details
properties.doc: Additional details about the status.

type.name: ResponseStatusDetails
type.doc: Base for all non-success response details.

properties.name: output
properties.doc: The list of output items generated by the response.

properties.name: usage
properties.doc:
Usage statistics for the Response, this will correspond to billing. A
VoiceLive API session will maintain a conversation context and append new
Items to the Conversation, thus output from previous turns (text and
audio tokens) will become the input for later turns.

type.name: ResponseTokenStatistics
type.doc: Overall usage statistics for a response.

properties.name: total_tokens
properties.doc: Total number of tokens (input + output).

properties.name: input_tokens
properties.doc: Number of input tokens.

properties.name: output_tokens
properties.doc: Number of output tokens.

properties.name: input_token_details
properties.doc: Detailed breakdown of input tokens.

properties.name: cached_tokens
properties.doc: Number of cached tokens used in the input.

properties.name: text_tokens
properties.doc: Number of text tokens used in the input.

properties.name: audio_tokens
properties.doc: Number of audio tokens used in the input.

properties.name: output_token_details
properties.doc: Detailed breakdown of output tokens.

properties.name: text_tokens
properties.doc: Number of text tokens generated in the output.

properties.name: audio_tokens
properties.doc: Number of audio tokens generated in the output.

properties.name: conversation_id
properties.doc:
Which conversation the response is added to, determined by the `conversation`
field in the `response.create` event. If `auto`, the response will be added to
the default conversation and the value of `conversation_id` will be an id like
`conv_1234`. If `none`, the response will not be added to any conversation and
the value of `conversation_id` will be `null`. If responses are being triggered
by server VAD, the response will be added to the default conversation, thus
the `conversation_id` will be an id like `conv_1234`.

properties.name: VoiceInternal
properties.doc: supported voice identifiers and configurations.

properties.name: ModalitiesInternal
properties.doc:
The set of modalities the model used to respond. If there are multiple modalities,
the model will pick one, for example if `modalities` is `["text", "audio"]`, the model
could be responding in either text or audio.

properties.name: output_audio_format
properties.doc: The format of output audio. Options are `pcm16`, `g711_ulaw`, or `g711_alaw`.

properties.name: temperature
properties.doc: Sampling temperature for the model, limited to [0.6, 1.2]. Defaults to 0.8.

properties.name: max_output_tokens
properties.doc:
Maximum number of output tokens for a single assistant response,
inclusive of tool calls, that was used in this response.

response.done.name: SessionUpdateResponseDone
response.done.doc:
Returned when a Response is done streaming. Always emitted, no matter the
final state. The Response object included in the `response.done` event will
include all output Items in the Response but will omit the raw audio data.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be `response.done`.

response.output_item.added.name: SessionUpdateResponseOutputItemAdded
response.output_item.added.doc: Returned when a new Item is created during Response generation.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be `response.output_item.added`.

properties.name: response_id
properties.doc: The ID of the Response to which the item belongs.

properties.name: output_index
properties.doc: The index of the output item in the Response.

response.output_item.done.name: SessionUpdateResponseOutputItemDone
response.output_item.done.doc:
Returned when an Item is done streaming. Also emitted when a Response is
interrupted, incomplete, or cancelled.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be `response.output_item.done`.

properties.name: response_id
properties.doc: The ID of the Response to which the item belongs.

properties.name: output_index
properties.doc: The index of the output item in the Response.

response.content_part.added.name: SessionUpdateResponseContentPartAdded
response.content_part.added.doc:
Returned when a new content part is added to an assistant message item during
response generation.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be `response.content_part.added`.

properties.name: response_id
properties.doc: The ID of the response.

properties.name: item_id
properties.doc: The ID of the item to which the content part was added.

properties.name: output_index
properties.doc: The index of the output item in the response.

properties.name: content_index
properties.doc: The index of the content part in the item's content array.

properties.name: part
properties.doc: The content part that was added.

response.content_part.done.name: SessionUpdateResponseContentPartDone
response.content_part.done.doc:
Returned when a content part is done streaming in an assistant message item.
Also emitted when a Response is interrupted, incomplete, or cancelled.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be `response.content_part.done`.

properties.name: response_id
properties.doc: The ID of the response.

properties.name: item_id
properties.doc: The ID of the item.

properties.name: output_index
properties.doc: The index of the output item in the response.

properties.name: content_index
properties.doc: The index of the content part in the item's content array.

properties.name: part
properties.doc: The content part that is done.

response.text.done.name: SessionUpdateResponseTextDone
response.text.done.doc:
Returned when the text value of a "text" content part is done streaming. Also
emitted when a Response is interrupted, incomplete, or cancelled.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be `response.text.done`.

properties.name: response_id
properties.doc: The ID of the response.

properties.name: item_id
properties.doc: The ID of the item.

properties.name: output_index
properties.doc: The index of the output item in the response.

properties.name: content_index
properties.doc: The index of the content part in the item's content array.

properties.name: text
properties.doc: The final text content.

response.audio_transcript.delta.name: SessionUpdateResponseAudioTranscriptDelta
response.audio_transcript.delta.doc: Returned when the model-generated transcription of audio output is updated.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be `response.audio_transcript.delta`.

properties.name: response_id
properties.doc: The ID of the response.

properties.name: item_id
properties.doc: The ID of the item.

properties.name: output_index
properties.doc: The index of the output item in the response.

properties.name: content_index
properties.doc: The index of the content part in the item's content array.

properties.name: delta
properties.doc: The transcript delta.

response.audio_transcript.done.name: SessionUpdateResponseAudioTranscriptDone
response.audio_transcript.done.doc:
Returned when the model-generated transcription of audio output is done
streaming. Also emitted when a Response is interrupted, incomplete, or
cancelled.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be `response.audio_transcript.done`.

properties.name: response_id
properties.doc: The ID of the response.

properties.name: item_id
properties.doc: The ID of the item.

properties.name: output_index
properties.doc: The index of the output item in the response.

properties.name: content_index
properties.doc: The index of the content part in the item's content array.

properties.name: transcript
properties.doc: The final transcript of the audio.

response.audio.done.name: SessionUpdateResponseAudioDone
response.audio.done.doc:
Returned when the model-generated audio is done. Also emitted when a Response
is interrupted, incomplete, or cancelled.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be `response.audio.done`.

properties.name: response_id
properties.doc: The ID of the response.

properties.name: item_id
properties.doc: The ID of the item.

properties.name: output_index
properties.doc: The index of the output item in the response.

properties.name: content_index
properties.doc: The index of the content part in the item's content array.

response.function_call_arguments.delta.name: SessionUpdateResponseFunctionCallArgumentsDelta
response.function_call_arguments.delta.doc: Returned when the model-generated function call arguments are updated.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be `response.function_call_arguments.delta`.

properties.name: response_id
properties.doc: The ID of the response.

properties.name: item_id
properties.doc: The ID of the function call item.

properties.name: output_index
properties.doc: The index of the output item in the response.

properties.name: call_id
properties.doc: The ID of the function call.

properties.name: delta
properties.doc: The arguments delta as a JSON string.

response.function_call_arguments.done.name: SessionUpdateResponseFunctionCallArgumentsDone
response.function_call_arguments.done.doc:
Returned when the model-generated function call arguments are done streaming.
Also emitted when a Response is interrupted, incomplete, or cancelled.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be `response.function_call_arguments.done`.

properties.name: response_id
properties.doc: The ID of the response.

properties.name: item_id
properties.doc: The ID of the function call item.

properties.name: output_index
properties.doc: The index of the output item in the response.

properties.name: call_id
properties.doc: The ID of the function call.

properties.name: arguments
properties.doc: The final arguments as a JSON string.

properties.name: name
properties.doc: The name of the function call.

response.animation_blendshapes.delta.name: SessionUpdateResponseAnimationBlendshapeDelta
response.animation_blendshapes.delta.doc: Represents a delta update of blendshape animation frames for a specific output of a response.

response.animation_blendshapes.done.name: SessionUpdateResponseAnimationBlendshapeDone
response.animation_blendshapes.done.doc: Indicates the completion of blendshape animation processing for a specific output of a response.

response.emotion_hypothesis.name: SessionUpdateResponseEmotionHypothesis
response.emotion_hypothesis.doc: Represents an emotion hypothesis detected from response audio with multiple candidates.

response.audio_timestamp.delta.name: SessionUpdateResponseAudioTimestampDelta
response.audio_timestamp.delta.doc: Represents a word-level audio timestamp delta for a response.

response.audio_timestamp.done.name: SessionUpdateResponseAudioTimestampDone
response.audio_timestamp.done.doc: Indicates completion of audio timestamp delivery for a response.

response.animation_viseme.delta.name: SessionUpdateResponseAnimationVisemeDelta
response.animation_viseme.delta.doc: Represents a viseme ID delta update for animation based on audio.

response.animation_viseme.done.name: SessionUpdateResponseAnimationVisemeDone
response.animation_viseme.done.doc: Indicates completion of viseme animation delivery for a response.

properties.name: type
properties.doc: The event type, must be 'session.avatar.connecting'.

properties.name: server_sdp
properties.doc: The server's SDP answer for the avatar connection.

parameters.name: contentType
parameters.doc: Body parameter's content type. Known values are application/json

parameters.name: contentType
parameters.doc: Body parameter's content type. Known values are application/json
